sec.p:
We found 5049 individuals of tabanid flies during the study period (
     
      Table 1
     ; 
     
      Data S1
     ). There was a wide range in the occurrence of species over time, with some appearing only in one date and others almost throughout the entire study period (
     
      Table 1
     ). Most species, however, occurred in a limited amount of dates: 8.1±1.8 dates (mean ± SE, n = 31 species). Likewise, species abundance also showed a wide range, with some species contributing with only one individual during the study period and others contributing with many (
     
      Table 1
     ). Most individuals, however (96%), belonged to just six species, which yielded a low evenness index for this assemblage (
     
      E
      = 0.07).
